\@writefile{lof}{\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {1}{\ignorespaces 1D KRR Example with Gaussian noise. Observation: $\lambda =10^{-1}$ is too smooth (underfit), failing to capture the peak and trough of the sine wave. $\lambda =10^{-8}$ is too wiggly (overfit), matching the noise in the samples. $\lambda =10^{-4}$ provides a good balance, capturing $f_0(x)$ without overfitting the noise, illustrating the balance discussed in 2(b).}}{4}{figure.caption.17}\protected@file@percent }
