\newlabel{fig:krr}{{1}{4}{1D KRR Example with Gaussian noise. Observation: $\lambda =10^{-1}$ is too smooth (underfit), failing to capture the peak and trough of the sine wave. $\lambda =10^{-8}$ is too wiggly (overfit), matching the noise in the samples. $\lambda =10^{-4}$ provides a good balance, capturing $f_0(x)$ without overfitting the noise, illustrating the balance discussed in 2(b)}{figure.caption.17}{}}
